Material Information Summary

  • Exploration Update: Initial fieldwork commenced at Sybil (Francis Creek prospect), with drilling planned for July–August 2025.
  • High-Grade Historical Samples:
  • Rock chip samples graded up to 907g/t Au and 262g/t Au at Francis Creek.
  • Bulk sample in 1991 yielded 961t @ 7.6g/t Au (235oz Au).
  • Geological Confidence: Vein textures and geochemical data support a thickening gold-rich "boiling zone" to the east/southeast.
  • Upcoming Catalysts:
  • RC drilling results for Plateau and Salla Au-Cu-Zn (July 2025).
  • Liontown Au resource upgrade and metallurgy results (July–August 2025).
  • RC drilling at Sybil (July–August 2025).

Key Points:

  • Exploration Update: Field mapping confirms upper levels of a copper porphyry system at surface in the Southern Porphyry target (Llahuin Project, Chile).
  • Next Steps:
  • Geophysical reprocessing (MAG, IP, MT) underway to refine drill targets (results expected in coming weeks).
  • Drilling contractors being secured, with Phase I drilling expected to commence Q4 2025.
  • Historic Drill Data: Re-logging supports porphyry hypothesis; notable intercepts include:
  • 5m at 0.48% CuEq (61–66m in hole 22LHRC024).

Deal Structure (JV):

  • FMR holds earn-in rights for up to 60% of the Southern Porphyry JV (tenements held by Southern Hemisphere Mining Ltd).

Key Material Information Summary

  • Drilling Program Extension: Extension of drilling at the Amadee Prospect, part of the Bousquet Project (Quebec, Canada), due to similarities with the high-grade Paquin Prospect.
  • Historical Mineralisation: Amadee drilling (1940) intersected 1.52m @ 6.8g/t Au, with surface samples up to 8.0g/t Au. Current drilling confirms smoky quartz veining at depth.
  • Exploration Upside: Potential for >1km mineralised structure linking Paquin and Amadee, with mineralization open along strike (>200m) and at depth.
  • Near-term Catalyst: First assay results expected mid-July 2025; further drilling planned to test western extension.

No capital raising, financials, or material corporate changes announced. Focus remains on exploration results and near-term catalysts.

Material Information Summary

Key Highlights (Resource Upgrade Announcement)

  • Resource Upgrade:
  • Total 151,000 oz Au and 902,000 oz Ag at 1.40 g/t Au and 8.4 g/t Ag, across 3.3Mt.
    • Indicated: 2.2Mt @ 1.40 g/t Au, 9.7 g/t Ag (67% of total).
    • Inferred: 1.1Mt @ 1.54 g/t Au, 6.6 g/t Ag.

  • 16% increase in gold resource vs. prior estimate.

  • Exploration Upside: Mineralization remains open along strike and at depth, with drilling planned to expand resources.

  • Strategic Impact:

  • Bolsters QMines’ hub-and-spoke production model in Central Queensland.
  • Combined JORC resources now ~20Mt across three 100%-owned projects.

Operational Context

  • Mt. Mackenzie will feed into the Mt. Chalmers processing plant (140km away), improving project economics.

Forward-Looking Notes

  • No immediate capital-raising or trading halt declared. Focus on resource growth and integration into mine planning.

Conclusion: Material for valuation due to increased resource scale, higher confidence (Indicated category dominance), and strategic synergies with existing assets.
